title: FIVE FINGERS 102 Dossier
description:
Five Fingers 102 - Dossier (10 Oct 1959)

Victor Sebastian was an American counterspy posing as a Communist agent in Europe. His code name was "Five Fingers" and his mission was to feed information on Communist activities to the United States Government. Sebastian&#039;s public cover was that of a theatrical booking agent who placed musical talent in clubs and cafes all over the continent. In this capacity he traveled with a beautiful young fashion model, Simone Genet, who aspired to become a singer. Romance blossomed between them, which complicated their relationship since she was not aware of his espionage activities. The only person who did know was Robertson, Sebastian&#039;s American contact. This series was loosely based on a successful 1952 film of the same name directed by Joseph L. Mankiewiez and starring James Mason and Danielle Darrieux.

In this episode, Sebastian is assigned to retrieve a manuscript that is reported to reveal the identity of many spies, including him. This was the first full hour-long episode, having been preceded by the half-hour pilot.

The video quality of this episode is very poor.

Stars:
David Hedison as Victor Sebastian
Luciana Paluzzi as Simone Genet
Paul Burke as Robertson

Principal Guest Stars:
Edgar Bergen as Joseph Heidegger
John Williams as Nicolas Constantine

Writer: Robert C. Dennis
Director: Montgomery Pittman
